HEADWORD: Spoilfive
<hw>Spoil"five`</hw> <pr>(spoil"f⟦imac⟧v`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
certain game at cards in which, if no player wins three of the five
tricks possible on any deal, the game is said to be
<xex>spoiled</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spoilful</ent>⟦br⟧
